dialog.label: Configure Gantt View Properties: User Settings

helpgrid.innerhtml: Specify the properties to display in the data table of the Gantt view. The settings will affect the current schedule.

dialog.label: Configure Gantt View Properties: Default Settings

helpgrid.innerhtml: Specify the default properties for display in the data table of the Gantt view. These settings apply to all schedules.
Define the relationship between the work records, which will determine the scheduling order.
Modify existing work record data by entering or modifying information in any field. A value entered into a field in the mass update section updates all selected work rows with that value.
Define the parameters that you want the optimization model to take into account when assigning labor and crews. The template can be used to optimize any work list.

Define the parameters that you want the optimization model to take into account when assigning labor and crews based on there location and work location. The template can be used to optimize any work list.

Enter the details for your optimization server. Enter the URL of the optimization server and the optimization model repository information. Each optimization model listed must have its own user name and password in the Optimization Model.
You must create one new user in the database for each optimization model. The user and its associated schema cannot be used for any other purpose.
To display the Crew assignments for this Labor during a specific date range, select a start date and end date.

helpgrid.innerhtml: To find labor available during a specific date range, enter the dates in the From and To fields. To include labor who are already assigned to other jobs, select Include Fully Assigned.
